---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Inguz Care" description="How we handle and protect personal data collected via this website.">
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500"><strong>Last updated:</strong> August 2025</p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Who we are</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Inguz Care (“we”, “us”) provides residential care for children and young people in England &amp; Wales.
      This policy explains how we handle personal data collected through this website.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What data we collect via this website</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">When you submit our contact form, we collect only the details you provide:</p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li><strong>First name</strong> (required)</li>
      <li><strong>Last name</strong> (required)</li>
      <li><strong>Email address</strong> (required)</li>
      <li><strong>Phone number</strong> (optional)</li>
      <li><strong>Your message</strong> (the text you type into the form)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
      We do not ask for or require special category data through the website form. Please avoid sharing sensitive information in your message.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How we use your data</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>To respond to your enquiry and provide information you’ve requested</li>
      <li>To maintain site security and performance (e.g., logs to diagnose issues)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Our lawful bases for processing</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — responding to enquiries and operating our website</li>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong> — for any optional follow-up communications you explicitly agree to receive (you can withdraw consent at any time)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Who processes your data</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We use reputable service providers to run this website. They act as our processors and only process your data under our instructions:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li><strong>Website hosting &amp; delivery:</strong> our site is hosted on a global content delivery network.</li>
      <li><strong>Contact form handling:</strong> form submissions are delivered to us via a secure form service and then by email to our team.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
      We do not sell your personal data. We may disclose information where required by law or to protect rights, safety and security.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">International transfers</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Some providers may process data on servers outside the UK/EEA. Where this happens, appropriate safeguards are used (for example, standard contractual clauses) to protect your information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How long we keep your data</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We keep enquiry information for up to <strong>12 months</strong> after our last contact unless we need to keep it longer to manage an ongoing enquiry or where the law requires a different period.
      After that, we delete it or anonymise it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Your rights</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">Under UK GDPR you can:</p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>Request access to your data</li>
      <li>Ask us to correct or delete it</li>
      <li>Object to or restrict our processing</li>
      <li>Ask for data portability</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent where processing relies on consent</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Children’s privacy</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      This website is intended for professionals, parents and carers. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children via the website. If a child contacts us, we will handle any information appropriately and sensitively.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Cookies and analytics</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We use only essential cookies required to operate this site. We do not use marketing cookies or third-party tracking by default.
      See our <a class="underline hover:text-[#5f7c7b]" href="/cookies">Cookies</a> page for details.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">How to contact us</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      For privacy requests or questions, email
      <a class="underline hover:text-[#5f7c7b]" href="mailto:hello@inguzcare.co.uk">InguzCare@outlook.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Complaints</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      If you have concerns about our use of your data, please contact us first. You also have the right to complain to the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO).
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We may update this page from time to time to reflect how we process personal data. We will post any changes here with a new “last updated” date.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-slate-500">
      This page provides general information and is not legal advice. Please ask a solicitor to review this policy for your particular operations.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
